The need for speed The Run is fighting all over America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race turns into a series of stupid mistakes of people who don't care about it into a routine morning shift at work.
It fulfills everyone's ambition to some extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do anything more.
The new subtitled The Run produced high expectations before it was released.
He promised to take a new direction with the race series Need for Speed already old and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how will be the added passages during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole is pulling down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught in the adventure of which the chief hero Jack has characteristic problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite different from each other and interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are surprisingly pretty even if the technical level of graphics is the same type as the previous series.
I mean, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition, from time to time, embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche doesn't fall on you.
Next to this the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the requested number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you will run against the time (classic duel with the chronometer) and then wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation worse for you.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
This is rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by typing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is quite the same because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enrich the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the concur the driving model goes very well with the type of racing design.
So it's all right.
The problems begin to appear after some time.
At the same time as the driving model is different, the collision model is not yet well developed.
We don't expect this game to cause complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don't have the slightest idea of how your car behaves in a collision with any object, it's not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy voltages.
Or you'll end up in pieces.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken the figure or you have come out in the setting the game will bring you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and the solution needs to be found by remembering the part of the route in question.
The big problem with this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that need to be passed in a certain way, otherwise this does not pass.
Otherwise you encounter "civilian" vehicles in a given location always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
What gets angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and conturner them or brake them.
It is equal if you go in front of him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents still have other advantages.
All the time of the game, you, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This is the most irritating at the end of the game when you ride on a long reverse-direction bridge.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in reverse direction and you collide many times.
We can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you are bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change cars during the races.
You should pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can switch cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cars for straight motorways and super sports cars with exotic attire on very technical pipelines, for example on yaw roads in the mountains.
And the fashion of challenges, which are races in particular places you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile, which is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects on-line with the Autolog function which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult strokes to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the tunnel of the subway (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km / hour (a priori) and behind you comes a subway train that sends you the car directly to the scrap metal.
In the writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really think we're idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is usually nice and in some cases really great.
What bothers us is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is at your choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the young audience a new sound track was created in the style "I mix everything," but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it's not over.
The fun is really good but get ready for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The velvet students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
For the third time, the Festa Academica festival offers festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from the higher and secondary schools.
The festival's highlight is composed of two concerts on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival the rector Vaclav Hampl sits," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choeur des lycées et classes secondaires which takes place with free entrance on 17 November from 14: 00 on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the programme is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University are performed.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop creative cooperation among young people.
The main organiser is the Czech Research Union in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, Msical meetings, student bonding and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the web pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
