Society was in the beginning great in the discovery of talents- as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus had the choice.
The current plan is completely in line with the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and is currently Chief Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM over the past few years does what we call jamy, brain- storming online from which came many future strategies and innovations.
It is not surprising that he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
