On the big companies that are falling apart:
Long before he revived Apple, Steve Jobs had anticipated how many industrial leaders would be mistaken and lose control of their market share.
"Let's say you were working at IBM or Xerox, you make a better copier or printer, and then what?"
You have a monopoly on the market, so the company is no more successful.
Sales and marketing can change it, so [it is these types of people] who eventually lead the companies and product specialists are excluded from decision-making.
The product genius that led to this monopoly position is completely rotten by people who can't imagine designing a good product compared to a bad product - the manual work required.
