Casino forgives Jonás Larrazábal and this one will be released
After 72 days of provisional arrest, Casino Red's legal power-holder granted forgiveness to the brother of the mayor of Monterrey for the trial initiated against him for alleged blackmail
After spending 72 years arrested, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the founder of Casino Red's legal power grants him forgiveness before the Second Criminal Court of the District, which follows a blackmail trial against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey.
After the attack at the Casino Royale, Casino Red owner Sergio Gil García published a series of photos and videos in which Manuel Jonás allegedly required him to pay an economic quote for the mayor of Monterrey to allow the clandestine operation of the gambling house.
Following the public denunciation, the Public Prosecutor's Office opened a criminal trial against the brother of the mayor of PANISTA and on 2 September he was arrested and kept under provisional arrest for 30 days.
After four hours in front of the Public Prosecutor's Office 3 of Penal Offences, he was transferred to Detention Centre 1, located in the Old District of the State Capital.
He remained there for the following 49 days when he was given a second detention order after the officer of the Public Prosecutor's Office rejected the offences of corruption and organized crime.
On October 19 he was transferred to the Cadereyta penal centre allegedly for blackmailing the owners of Casino Red with a million and a half pesos; but he spent only a few hours in the medium security detention centre because there were death threats against him.
The authorities allowed him to continue the closed trial in the municipal cells of San Nicolás de los Garza.
On 25 October an order of capture was issued by the registrar of the Second Criminal Court of the District, Jorge Yánez, who said that after almost two months of investigation there was sufficient confirmed evidence to determine the guilt of Jonás, such as that relating to the receipt of 1.5 million pesos of representatives of the gambling house in exchange for allowing its operation.
This Monday, the founder of the legal power of Casino Red, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, appeared before Judge José Luis Pecina to seek forgiveness for the brother of the mayor of the region; therefore he could recover his freedom in the following hours.
During the legal formalities, the Public Prosecutor attached to the Tribunal, Ramiro Arias, questioned García Gómez whether the damage had been recovered and who the partners of the gambling house had been the one who had granted the pardon, but the lawyer tried not to communicate the name.
According to file 197 / 2011, Jonás Larrazábal is granted legal forgiveness and subsequently no claim can be made in connection with the trial against him; he will not be asked for any compensation for the damage and no punishment.
After the hearing of the founder of the legal power of the gambling house, at 15: 50 hours the immediate freedom of Larrazabal Bretón was ordered.
The Registrar of the Tribunal, Jorge Yánez, moved to the prison of the municipality of San Nicolás de los Garza to inform Jonás that he had been legally forgiven and his case would be closed.
He will also communicate to him the immediate order of liberty issued by the judge.
