The Communications and Transportation Secretariat (TBS) has informed that the results of the accident in which the Secretary of Government, Francisco Blake Mora and other seven people lost their lives indicate that the helicopter shocked directly against the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to try a forced landing.
