The Committee of Experts also calls for health professionals to be trained in the duty to respect a denial of end-of-life care, without fear of criminal prosecution.
In the area of palliative care, the Committee calls for governments, health care institutions, and physicians to work together to ensure better palliative care beyond cancer cases.
Finally, with respect to palliative or terminal sedation, which is already widely used in Canadian health care institutions, the Committee requests that it be considered, when it is not used to reduce physical pain, as euthanasia, and that it be subject to the same procedures.
