"This opens the door to a situation where everyone who is tired of life and over 18 years of age could ask for help to commit suicide," said Mr. Deschamps, who had consulted yesterday a summary of the report.
Mr. Deschamps also points out that the authors of the report seem to place the autonomy of the person above all other values that participate in the social fabric of society.
"In society," he said, "there are beacons and constraints."
Health law expert Margaret Somerville also expressed "strong opposition" to the findings of the report, which she described as a "pro-euthanasia manifesto."
