The arrangements adopted by the Austrian Government are similar to the "German model," since Germany was the first European country to adopt such a "rule."
By 2017, the structural government deficit will have to fall by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, from 2017, the structural government deficit of the federal government will not have to exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional states and municipalities will have to present balanced budgets.
The aim is to bring public debt under the 60% criterion laid down in the Maastricht Treaty by 2020 / 21.
